    "sections": {
        "description": "<p>Blog Avatar Plugin allows site admins to upload avatars for their blog</p>\n<h4>How it works:-</h4>\n<p>Upload blog avatar from backend settings options.</p>\n<h4>Help &amp; Support</h4>\n<p>Please leave a comment on our blog <a href=\"http://buddydev.com/buddypress/add-avatars-to-your-blogs-on-buddypresswordpress-multisite-network/\" rel=\"nofollow ugc\">BuddyDev</a> for any suggestions, support request.<br />\nPlease leave a comment on <a href=\"http://buddydev.com/buddypress/add-avatars-to-your-blogs-on-buddypresswordpress-multisite-network/\" rel=\"nofollow ugc\">BuddyDev</a></p>\n",
        "installation": "<p>This section describes how to install the plugin and get it working.</p>\n<p>e.g.<br />\n1. Download the zip file and extract<br />\n1. Upload <code>blog-avatar</code> directory to the <code>/wp-content/plugins/</code> directory<br />\n1. Activate the plugin through the &#8216;Plugins&#8217; menu.<br />\n1. Enjoy</p>\n",
        "faq": "\n<h4>Does This plugin works without BuddyPress</h4>\n<p>\n<p>No, It needs you to have BuddyPress Installed and activated</p>\n</p>\n\n",
